ci_support_linux_64_nodejs20python3.10._:
c_compiler:
- gcc
c_compiler_version:
- '14'
c_stdlib:
- sysroot
c_stdlib_version:
- '2.17'
channel_sources:
- conda-forge/label/rust_dev,conda-forge
channel_targets:
- conda-forge main
cxx_compiler:
- gxx
cxx_compiler_version:
- '14'
docker_image:
- quay.io/condaforge/linux-anvil-x86_64:alma9
nodejs:
- '20'
openssl:
- '3.5'
pin_run_as_build:
  python:
    min_pin: x.x
    max_pin: x.x
python:
- 3.10.* *_cpython
rust_compiler:
- rust
target_platform:
- linux-64
zip_keys:
- - c_compiler_version
  - cxx_compiler_version
name: getdaft
raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: "getdaft"
  version: "0.6.13"

package:
  name: ${{ name | lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/Eventual-Inc/Daft/archive/refs/tags/v${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ff2705e21dcdbfc60ac8e8e363fc17d405a54c753b2f1c792a7ea45776ec1303

build:
  number: 0

requirements:
  build:
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - ${{ compiler('rust') }}
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - python
        - maturin >=1.5.0,<2.0.0
    - pkg-config
    - make
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
    - if: unix
      then: unzip
    - nodejs
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - maturin >=1.5.0,<2.0.0
    - openssl
    - xz-tools
  run:
    - python
    - pyarrow >=8.0.0
    - fsspec
    - tqdm
    - typing_extensions >=4.0.0
    - packaging

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - daft
  - script:
      - pip check
    requirements:
      run:
        - pip

about:
  license: Apache-2.0
  summary: Distributed Dataframes for Multimodal Data
  license_file:
    - LICENSE
    - THIRDPARTY.yml
  homepage: https://www.getdaft.io/
  repository: https://github.com/Eventual-Inc/Daft
  documentation: https://www.getdaft.io/projects/docs/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - thewchan
    - whophil
